# AnduinOS Butterfly - Post-installation configuration package

AnduinOS Butterfly is a modified version of AnduinOS (Ubuntu based), which is
designed to ease the transition from Windows 11. The Butterfly version comes
with an additional PPA from kelebek333 and several improvements for the comfort of use.

This package installs and configures a set of scripts and desktop launchers
to improve the out-of-the-box experience on AnduinOS Butterfly.

## Installed files

### Scripts — /usr/local/bin/

| Script | Role |
|--------|------|
| fix-power-butterfly.sh | Disables automatic sleep and screen lock at each login |
| fix-keyboard-butterfly-fr_FR.sh | Fixes French keyboard layout (fr_FR) at each login |
| wake-touchpad-butterfly.sh | Restores touchpad after suspend |
| install-libdvd-dvd-butterfly.sh | Improved libdvd-pkg installation assistant |
| setup-media-handling-butterfly.sh | Configures removable multimedia handling via dconf (run at install) |
| welcome-butterfly.sh | First-boot welcome script |
| toggle-power-butterfly.sh | Toggles the power management fix on or off |
| general-cleaning-butterfly.sh | Deep cleaning tool — removes junk files and vacuums browser databases. Run manually and deliberately, including before ISO rebuild. |
| install-kelebek333-butterfly.sh | Installs the PPA, and the packages Warpinator, Webapp-Manager and Hypnotix alltogether |

### Autostart — /etc/xdg/autostart/

These desktop files are launched automatically at each GNOME session:

- fix-power-butterfly.desktop
- fix-keyboard-butterfly-fr_FR.desktop
- wake-touchpad-butterfly.desktop
- welcome-butterfly.desktop

### Applications launchers in /usr/share/applications/

These entries appear in the GNOME application menu:

- install-libdvd-pkg-butterfly.desktop
- wake-touchpad-butterfly-manual.desktop
- welcome-butterfly-prefs.desktop
- toggle-power-butterfly.desktop

### System in /usr/share/polkit-1/actions/

- butterfly.toggle-power.policy : it allows toggle-power-butterfly to run
without a password prompt via pkexec for the active user, while requiring
administrator authentication for inactive sessions or remote access.
- butterfly.install-libdvd-pkg.policy : it allows install-libdvdcss2-butterfly
to be launched via pkexec with administrator authentication.

### The welcome script French translation
- welcome-butterfly_fr.mo to /usr/share/locale/fr/LC_MESSAGES/welcome-butterfly.mo

### The install-libdvd-pkg-butterfly script French translation
- install-libdvd-pkg-butterfly_fr.mo to /usr/share/locale/fr/LC_MESSAGES/install-libdvd-pkg-butterfly.mo

## Additional software

This package provides a script to install the kelebek333 PPA and 3 packages,
announced by the welcome script:

  ppa:kelebek333/mint-tools

This PPA provides among else:
- Warpinator: file sharing over local network (compatible with Winpinator on Windows)
- Webapp-Manager: to create desktop launchers for websites
- Hypnotix: IPTV player

Reference: https://launchpad.net/~kelebek333/+archive/ubuntu/mint-tools

